tweet: Playing some of their best soccer of the season Richmond heads into the half beating Villanova 3-1.
Natalie LeClair beats the keeper on the breakaway with a chip shot to put the Spiders ahead 3-1
That was also Bernetich's first career score
Dana Bernetich toe-pokes Richmond ahead with her score following a corner kick in the 38' minute
That match-tying score was Miller's first career goal
Richmond's Violet Miller ties up the game on an unassisted volley
Villanova strikes first in the second minute with a goal from Caitlin Forte assisted by Hiedi Sabatura
Starting for the Spiders are, Bernetich, Parisi, Miller, LeClair, Lescalleet, Smith, Koczot, Lybert, Williams, Riefner, and Young
Home opener TONIGHT at Robins Stadium at 7 p.m. Come out and support #SpiderSoccer against Villanova!
#USWNT advances to U-20 World Cup semifinal against Nigeria after gutsy win over PRK!
RT @ussoccer_ynt: The USA is on to the semifinal in Tokyo where it will face Nigeria! What a gutsy performance by this young U.S. squad! ...
Spiders Host Villanova In Home Opener Friday At Robins Stadium http://t.co/ZGPmN14O
Recap from tonight's loss to the Tribe on the road in Williamsburg. http://t.co/FZrAXbFI
Final Spider team stats: 10 shots (2 SOG), 1 corner, 7 saves.
Final Spider stats: LeClair (3 shots), Koczot/Williams (2 shots each), Miller/Lescalleet/Alvarez (1 shot each), Young (7 saves)
The Spiders will turn right around and welcome Villanova to Robins Stadium for their home-opener on Friday at 7.
Schaffer heads a corner into the back of the net to give Tribe the 3-0 win.
Plattenberg slips ball to Barry from right, which she easily slides into back of net from near left post. 2-0 Tribe w/ less than 4 to play.
Liberatore dribbles through the box and slips a shot into the right pocket. 1-0 Tribe with 9:32 to play in 2nd half.
Teams battling for momentum throughout the better part of the 2nd half. We remain scoreless at the 17:00 mark.
Alvarez with a header off a Koczot free kick that clangs off the crossbar. LeClair with the put-back, but it's quickly cleared.
Riefner sends it to far right of box, where Williams collects & sends just high. Young w/ another fine save on the opposite side.
Irvin with a blast to center net, where Young was able to deflect above the crossbar. Tribe corner.
Schaffer with a shot early here in the 2nd half, but Young comes out with the save.
Spider 1st-half stats: Lescalleet & Williams each w/ 1 SOG. Miller, LeClair & Koczot w/ a shot apiece. Young w/ 2 saves.
Spiders try to get something going before the half, but can't get a shot off prior to the whistle. Scoreless heading into the half, folks.
We're still scoreless here with 6:30 to play in the 1st half.
Rutter with a shot that sails well high of the goal as the Tribe continues to control much of possession as of late.
Young with pair of solid saves after Schaffer sends a ball to the left of net before taking rebound from a few yards out just moments later.
Schaffer's rocket from 25 out skies just high  of the net. Tribe controlling much of the play now.
Schaffer sends a nice ball to left of net, but Liberatore couldn't get a head on it. W&M back on possession following the goal kick.
Lescalleet gets rebound on Spider corner & fires to center net, where Casey was waiting to make the save. Spider offense now getting going.
Schaffer with a good shot on goal off a Tribe corner, but Young collects to end the threat.
Williams w/ great shot on goal after Smith sent to her inside box. Casey makes the save with relative ease. We're scoreless at 39:00 mark.
We're underway in tonight's match. Spiders will need to watch the Tribe attack & especially preseason #CAA Player of Year Mallory Schaffer.
Tonight's Tribe starters: Fredrickson, Heck, Liberatore, Barry, Rutter, Shaughnessy, Schaffer, Bristol, Harpe, Irvin & Casey in goal
Tonight's Spider starters: Bernetich, Miller, LeClair, Lescalleet, Smith, Layne, Koczot, Lybert, Williams, Reifner & Young in goal
Follow us throughout tonight's 7 p.m. match against the Tribe here in Williamsburg. Live stats also available at http://t.co/NucIDies
Spiders Travel To William & Mary Wednesday http://t.co/Se2AibWX
#USA fell to Germany but will advance to quarters Aug. 31 at 2:50 ET against winner of Group C. Follow @ussoccer_ynt for coverage.
Next up for the Spiders is a Wednesday matchup with William and Mary on the road in Williamsburg. Kickoff set for 7 p.m.
Lancers' Lindsey Ottavio strikes at the 9:02 in 2nd OT to give Longwood a 2-1 win.
After an exciting 1st OT period, we're still scoreless here in Farmville. On to the 2nd 10:00 OT after 2:00 break.
Lancers with a great look as they battle the Spider backline. Shot sent across the box, but Longwood's Kelsey McDonald can't get a touch.
Violet Miller with a shot at the top of the box that sails just high. 7:30 remaining in 1st OT.
Shondel Archer escapes inside, but Lancers' keeper Byron immediately steps in  to clear. 8:00 to play in 1st OT.
Now underway in the 1st 10:00 OT session. Williams looking to create a play early, sending it into the box, but no one home.
Spiders and Lancers end regulation with the score tied 1-1. Quick 5:00 break before heading into the 1st OT period.
LeClair serves corner to Williams, who drives header to upper right of net. Spiders all square, 1-1, with Lancers with 11:00 to play.
Williams sends shot just wide left as we're now under 22:00 in tonight's 2nd half. Lancers lead 1-0.
